description:
Set 1

Day Job, Minglewood Blues, Dire Wolf, Beat It On Down The Line, West L.A. Fadeaway, It's All Over Now, Bird Song, Hell In A Bucket-> Don't Ease Me In

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain-> Estimated Prophet-> Drums-> The Wheel-> Truckin'-> Goin' Down The Road Feelin' Bad-> Around & Around-> Good Lovin', E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
Outstanding Upgrade Pristine quality upgrade over the AUDs available, thanx to Charlie. Must-hear Scarlet>Fire and mesmerizing Birdsong.

Get this.

Fire..Fire...|Fire Mickey Hart brought out the talking drum during Fire on the Mountain then came the Echo/Effects to close out the song. It was the best of times. Roadtrip to Hampton with 4 college buddies. Hotel room next to the spaceship for the weekend. WOW!
Fun Show Nothing over the top, No Highlights
Ignore Review Below Show SMOKES! Both nights do.  Best of that tour.

Estimated? Did I review this one somewhere... I was reading a review of a show from 81 and someone was commenting on Jerry's frustration at Bobby's "style"
It brought to mind this show... High as a kite, again, but Bobby's screams during the jam in Estimated was absolutely hilarious! I remember bursting out laughing thinking it was the funniest thing. Likely it wasn't the only time Bobby did it... right, right? They were tearing it up that night!
